-- Japanese Bought Net 538.5 Billion Yen Overseas Debt Last Week
-- B y   M i n h   B u i
-- 2012-06-06T23:52:07Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-06/japanese-bought-net-538-5-billion-yen-overseas-debt-last-week.html
Japanese investors were net
buyers of foreign bonds during the week ended June 1 according
to figures based on reports from designated major investors
released by the Ministry of Finance in  Tokyo .  Japanese investors bought 538.5 billion yen ($6.8 billion)
in overseas bonds and notes, bought 205.2 billion yen in overseas stocks
and bought 72.5 billion yen in overseas short term securities.
That results in a total net purchase of 816.2 billion yen.  Foreign investors bought 1023 billion yen in Japanese bonds,
sold 74.7 billion yen in stocks, and bought 474.6 billion yen in
short term securities, resulting in a total net purchase of 1422.9
billion yen.    To contact the reporter on this story:
Minh Bui in Sydney at   mbui@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
